[1]
Date: Thu, 10 Apr 1997 09:01:06 -0700
From: marcof@mail.usfq.edu.ec (Marco Fronasini)
Subject: Re: PRO/AH>(2) Leishmaniasis, canine - Italy: advice needed
I am a Dr. from Ecuador. I recently got acquinted with the preliminary
results of a clinical trial on cutaneous Leishmaniasis from a local research
group (Dr. Ronald Guderian from Hospital Voz Andes). This research group is
having important remission rates in the treatment of cutaneous Leishmaniasis
with MEFLOQUINE which is an antimalarial drug used for chloroquine-resistant
P. falciparum.
---
Marco Fornasini
Professor of Epidemiology
